is also very important for that reason that after 1.e4 e5 2.Nf3 Nc6 3.Bc4 Nf6
4.d4 (we don't have to play this way, but this is an interesting theoretical
line) 4...d6!? is rather interesting, reaching the same position!} 5. dxe5 {
This is the most straightforward choice.} (5. d5 {I think White is definitely
better here, but after} Ne7 6. Bd3 g6 7. c4 Bg7 8. Nc3 {While I like the
position itself, I don't like the fact it is a very KID-looking position,
which has nothing to do with the positions we typically get in our repertoire.
So, we don't wanna go here, at least as our main repertoire choice. But, if
