not only do we get the center, but also, we don't even let him finish his
development as we have a lovely active continuation} 8. Qb3 {The f7-pawn is a
huge weakness, which is a fairly typical situation in the open games, overall.}
Nh6 9. d4 {Now the h6-knight is under attack. Retreating definitely isn't an
option unless Black wants to lose that little guy on f7.} O-O 10. Bxh6 gxh6 11.
Nd5 {White's huge advantage is undeniable. I would be seriously considering
