analysis short.}) (5... Nf6 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. e5 {The position is just terrible
here as the knight is getting kicked back and Black needs to lose even more
time. White's fantastic e5-pawn does not hurt his chances, either.}) 6. Qxd4
Nf6 7. e5 {The knight is getting kicked away. As a result, White gets three
extra pieces in the game as well as the space advantage: I would already go as
far as claiming that White is winning. I know it's a good time to stop the
analysis, but let me give a short line to show how we finish Black off.} Nh7 8.
Nc3 Be7 9. Qg4 Ng5 10. Qg3 {White avoided any possible x-rays over the h3-c8
