White has somewhat more space, but the bishop is misplaced on c4. And, very
importantly, the positions are very atypical of the Italian - that is
definitely a good enough reason against this move, already. In the endgame
after 5.dxe5, though, Black also pretends he's doing fine. That position is
definitely solid, but I think White is surely able to keep some very neat
pressure.} (4... exd4 {It's possible to play this way, but after} 5. Nxd4 {
We get our typical advantage thanks to the e4-pawn which is way more useful
than the Black d6-pawn. It's currently on d7, of course, but it will need to
go to d6. We get our typical advantage thanks to the e4-pawn which is way more
