several extra units in the game. Sounds fairly attractive!}) 13. Bxd5 Ba7 14.
O-O d6 15. Bxb7 {For example, grabbing a pawn sounds like a good idea!}) 10. c3
{We immediately force transition to a highly beneficial endgame.} Nxf3+ 11.
Qxf3 Qxf3 12. gxf3 cxd6 13. Rg1 g6 14. Bd5 {White kept some nagging edge, as
Black is totally passive. Getting out would involve some material sacrifices,
this is a terrible position to be in. Again, if you have any doubts, ask the
a8-rook's opinion! 1/2 (58) Antal,G (2563) - Andriasian,Z (2611) chess.com INT
2020} *

