or Rg3 is about to come and crush Black. This is simply terrible!}) 18. Bxf6
gxf6 19. Rd3 {This rook lift looks really good. What should Black do as all
the sorts of threats are coming up? Man, this is very dangerous. I know the
computer will hold a draw and that I cannot argue with the God of chess which
claims 0.00, but that's not the point of my work. The point is to help you win,
and with such preparation, you will!!} *

