monarch. At the same time, Black's a5-knight is woeful and he is still a pawn
down! The position remains incredibly complicated, but White is a pawn up and
he does have active ideas, such as Ne3, Rb5!, etc - I believe White is better,
objectively. Yet, we again get to see this isn't a variation for the
faint-hearted, you need some guts here - that's for sure!}) 17... c4 {This
amazing blockading move is the only way for Black to get counterplay. I would
