{White is just threatening to take that e4-pawn, while after} exd3 21. Qxd3 f4
22. Ne4 {White is just winning as ideas like Ba3 and Rd1 are coming and Black
has no counterplay. Right now his bishop is hanging, and it's not possible to
move it as Bxf4 would pick another free pawn. Besides that, White is already a
pawn up! So, things look terrible here for Black.}) 18. Re1 {White could play
Bf3 immediately, too, but it's nice to improve the rook first - it's going to
be rather restraining Black's activity over the e-file and stopping all the
