pieces are hanging and the queen is stuck.} 19. Bf3 Ba6 20. Nf1 {The bishop is
going to g2, while the knight will come to e3 and d5! I don't believe Black
can claim full compensation here - indeed, it's not easy to break through and
convert the pawn, but his compensation is more of a defensive/constraining
character - we and only we are the ones playing for a win here. By the way,
once again, this d3-d4 idea could prove reasonable in the future. Possibly,
