continue either with Rb1, or with Rfd1 and Kf1-e2, improving our king and
challenging Black on the open files. The c-pawn might also start running quite
soon!}) 16. Nxd4 exd4 17. Bxd7 Qxd7 18. Qxd4 {White is a healthy pawn up and
d5 is weak, this is just terrible for Black.}) 15. Bxc6 Bxc6 16. Nd4 {The
knight is attacking all the sensitive spots in opponent's camp - the bishop,
the f5-pawn and the e6-square.} Bd7 17. Qh5+ {A very important move. Had Black
castled, we won't be nearly as happy.} g6 18. Qh6 {Black still has a hard time
